Reasoning: The paper focuses on analyzing and understanding the behavior of Pathogenic Social Media (PSM) accounts and their impact on social media platforms. This involves techniques related to social media analysis, information retrieval, and natural language processing, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
